<h1 class="main header bluemadness">We Love Capybaras</h1>
<img src="https://soranews24.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2014/04/cb-1.png" alt="capybara">

<body>
    <div class="background" h2>What are capybaras?</h2>
        <p>Capybaras are large semiaquatic South American rodents. They are the largest rodents in the world. Capybaras
            are short haired, brown rodents with short legs, small ears, and visibly no tail. They reside near lakes and
            rivers. There are two types of capybaras: lesser capybara and greater capybara. Lesser capybara is smaller.</p>
        >
    </div>
    <h2>What do Capybaras eat?</h2>
   <img src="https://thekidshouldseethis.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/capybara-nagasaki-biopark-pumpkins-01.jpg" alt="Capybaras eating a pumpkin">
   <p>Capybaras are vegetarians and eat aroound 3%-4% of their bdoyweight everyday(around six to eight pounds). Some foods include:</p>
   <ul>
    <li>Aquatic plants</li>
    <li>Plant roots</li>
    <li>Hay</li>
    <li>Crowngrass</li>
    <li>Switchgrass</li>
    <li>Sugar cane</li>
    <li>Barks</li>
 </ul>

    
    
    


